<h2>The weather in March 2018</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
In March 2018 daily average and maximum temperatures were much below average over almost all of Europe. In Central and Northern Europe also daily minimum temperatures were below average, but in Southern Europa they were above average. In a large part of Spain the day-night temperature difference was much below average, as maximum temperatures were exceptionally below and minimum temperatures were (much) above average.
